title: McCarthy becomes first speaker ever to be ousted from job in House vote
description: House Speaker Kevin McCarthy was voted out of his position in an unprecedented move by hard-right conservatives, causing chaos within the Republican leadership. McCarthy's rival, Rep. Matt Gaetz, led the charge to remove him, garnering support from conservative Republicans and Democrats who believed McCarthy was unfit for leadership.

title: 45-day covert op, financial probe culminated in NewsClick raids
description: The Delhi Police's special cell conducted a covert investigation for 45 days before launching raids on NewsClick, a web portal, and arresting its editor-in-chief and human resources head. The investigation involved technical surveillance, financial analysis, and studying the portal's content. The suspects were categorized into three sections, with category A including the arrested duo and at least four more suspects. The raids were planned after a closed-door meeting and final briefing with the police commissioner. Around 400-450 police officers were involved in the operation, dividing into teams based on the suspect's profile.

title: TMC members detained in Delhi over stir at Krishi Bhavan
description: Trinamool Congress leaders, including Lok Sabha MP Abhishek Banerjee, were detained after staging a protest outside the office of junior minister for rural development Sadhvi Niranjan Jyoti. The minister had agreed to meet only a five-member delegation, but the party insisted on a meeting with the entire group.

title: 'Unwell' Ajit Pawar skips Delhi trip with CM, Fadnavis; but meets NCP men
description: Maharashtra Chief Minister Eknath Shinde and Deputy Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis traveled to New Delhi to meet with BJP leaders. This visit has sparked speculation about a potential cabinet expansion and discussions on reservation issues. There are also rumors of unhappiness within the alliance government, with Ajit Pawar's absence from the trip and reports of interference by his NCP group.

title: KCR wanted to join NDA, was rebuffed, says Modi in Telangana
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi claimed that Telangana Chief Minister K Chandrasekhar Rao (KCR) had approached him to join the NDA but was rejected, ahead of the state assembly polls. Modi also alleged that KCR wanted his son KT Rama Rao (KTR) to become the CM and retire himself. KCR's party, Bharat Rashtra Samithi (BRS), denied the allegations and accused Modi of dishonesty.

title: Govt issues draft norms to check student suicides
description: The Ministry of Education in India has issued draft guidelines to schools for supporting students who self-harm. The guidelines, known as UMMEED, aim to enhance sensitivity and understanding, and include measures such as setting up a School Wellness Team, identifying at-risk students, and providing immediate support. The guidelines also emphasize the importance of partnerships between schools, parents, and the community in preventing suicide and reducing stigma.

title: Jewar effect: Noida-YXP set to take off as IT hub
description: The construction of the Jewar airport in the Noida-Greater Noida-Yamuna Expressway (YXP) belt in Uttar Pradesh has made it a major investment destination for IT companies, telecom equipment manufacturers, and data centers. The region is expected to become a tech hub, competing with cities like Gurgaon, Bengaluru, Hyderabad, and Pune. Companies like Microsoft, Samsung, and Dixon Technologies have already invested in the area, and more are expected to follow. The upcoming airport is expected to further boost investments in the region.

title: BJP alleges irregularities but Nitish backs caste survey in Bihar
description: The opposition BJP in Bihar has alleged irregularities in the data collection process for the Bihar caste headcount, while its ally, Lok Janshakti Party (Ram Vilas), has called for a fresh survey. Leader of the opposition Vijay Kumar Sinha questioned why the government had not released the "report on the economic status of different castes".

title: Cops raid 100 locations linked to NewsClick, arrest founder
description: The editor-in-chief and human resources head of web portal NewsClick have been arrested by Delhi Police's Special Cell after raids at approximately 100 locations. The portal is being investigated for allegedly receiving illegal funding from China and disseminating Chinese propaganda. The police have seized electronic devices and documents during the raids.

title: Kerala priest joins BJP, defrocked
description: The Syro-Malabar Catholic Church in Kerala has temporarily relieved a senior parish member of his duties as vicar for joining the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP), in violation of rules preventing priests from associating with political parties. The church stated that this was a disciplinary measure and a commission will be formed to investigate the matter.

title: 961 arrested for child marriages in Assam
description: A total of 961 people were arrested in Assam for participating in child marriages, marking the second crackdown by the state government this year. Of those arrested, 551 were men who married underage girls, 351 were family members, and 14 were marriage solemnisers. The districts of Dhubri and Barpeta had the highest number of arrests. The previous crackdown resulted in over 3,000 arrests, with a total of 4,823 people now arrested in Assam for child marriages in the last five years.

title: Ashok Gehlot tenders unconditional apology for judiciary remarks
description: Rajasthan CM Ashok Gehlot has apologized to the high court over a PIL seeking contempt proceedings against him for remarks against the judiciary. Gehlot claimed that his comments were distorted by a publication and that he has never witnessed corruption in the judiciary. He requested the court to accept his apology and dismiss the PIL. The matter will be heard on November 7.

title: Thailand mall shooting: 'Teen gunman has mental illness'
description: A 14-year-old boy was arrested Tuesday after a shooting at a packed Bangkok mall that left two people dead and five wounded, and sent hundreds of panicked shoppers running in terror into the streets.Witnesses told AFP of chaotic scenes as shots rang out at the upmarket Siam Paragon mall in the heart of the Thai capital around 4:30 pm (0930 GMT).

title: IAF poised with 'better tactics' along China front: Chief
description: The IAF is ready with `better tactics and techniques’ to deal with challenges in places along the frontier where it cannot counter China’s `might or numbers’, even as the force plans to induct fighters, helicopters, missiles and radars worth Rs 2.5 to 3 lakh crore in the next seven to eight years to tackle the collusive China-Pakistan threat, Air Chief Marshal V R Chaudhari said on Tuesday.

title: Bihar caste survey: A double-edged sword for Nitish?
description: The recently released caste survey in Bihar may have mixed implications for Chief Minister Nitish Kumar. While it allows him to claim credit for the exercise's success and potentially gain political advantage, the survey also reveals that his own caste, the Kurmis, only make up 2.87% of the state's population. This vulnerability opens him up to attacks.

title: Webb telescope finds ‘Jupiter-sized’ planets floating in space
description: The James Webb Space Telescope has discovered Jupiter-sized free-floating planets that do not orbit a star. These objects, known as Jupiter Mass Binary Objects (JuMBOs), were identified during a survey of the Orion Nebula. The discovery has left astronomers perplexed as it challenges existing theories of star and planetary formation. The JuMBOs are approximately one million years old and have infernal surface temperatures of around 1,000 degrees Celsius.

title: Pictures: New Vande Bharat concept train with sleeper coaches
description: The upcoming sleeper version of Vande Bharat trains in India will feature improved suspension and lighting to enhance comfort for long-distance journeys. The first prototype train is set to be unveiled in February 2023, with interiors designed to prioritize passenger comfort.

title: TMC workers hold protests seeking MGNREGA dues
description: Members of Mamata Banerjee's Trinamool Congress (TMC) party protested in Delhi against the non-payment of central dues to West Bengal. The TMC has accused the BJP-led government of withholding Rs 15,000 crore in dues under the MGNREGA and PM Awaas Yojana. The protest came after a two-hour dharna at Rajghat on Mahatma Gandhi's birth anniversary.

title: UK visa fee hike effective this week: How will it impact Indians?
description: The British government is set to increase visa fees, making travel to the UK more expensive for people worldwide, including Indians. The price hike will affect visit visas under six months and student visas, with fees increasing by £15 and £127 respectively. The Home Office justifies the increase as necessary to fund public services and contribute to public sector pay.

title: When IndiGo ‘forgot’ an aged couple t Istanbul airport
description: An elderly couple were left stranded at Istanbul Airport for 24 hours after IndiGo failed to put them on their connecting flight to India. The couple, who have medical conditions and are vegetarians, were not provided with any assistance or communication by the airline. They spent the entire duration on chairs at the airport with limited food and drink.

title: NewsClick founder arrested in foreign funding case
IAF video gives glimpses of Gaganyaan astronauts
description: The Indian Air Force has released an official video showcasing the astronauts selected for India's first human spaceflight mission, Gaganyaan. The identities of the astronauts have been kept secret, but the video confirms that they are part of the Gaganyaan mission. It is yet to be determined whether the mission will carry two or three astronauts, and one of them may even go to the International Space Station as part of a collaboration between India and the US.

title: Satya-Sundar friendship a casualty amid Microsoft vs Google
description: Testifying at an anti-trust trial brought against Google by the federal government, Nadella never once took Pichai's name, but skewered the tech giant (even though Microsoft is bigger in terms of market cap $2.38 trillion v $1.69 trillion), saying Google's dominance of online search is making it harder for competitors like Microsoft’s Bing to gain a foothold because the Silicon Valley giant uses its power to monopolize publishers and advertisers. Microsoft is headquartered in Redmond, Washington, outside Seattle.

title: Rochelle Rao and Keith Sequeira blessed with a baby girl
description: Rochelle Rao and Keith Sequiera have welcomed their baby girl, born on October 1st. Rochelle shared the news on Instagram, along with a cute photo of the baby's feet. The couple had previously expressed their excitement during Rochelle's baby shower, thanking their friends and family for their support.  Take a look:

title: Canada not looking to escalate situation with India: Trudeau
Parul, Annu win gold as track & field athletes shine at Asian Games
description: India's Parul Chaudhary and Annu Rani clinch gold medals in women's 5000m and javelin throw events respectively as the track and field athletes claimed a total of 6 medals on Day 10 of the Asian Games in Hangzhou. It was the second medal for Parul at the Games as she earlier claimed a silver in the women's 3000m steeplechase.

title: Amritpal Singh on indefinite hunger strike in Assam jail
description: Amritpal Singh, the self-proclaimed Sikh religious preacher and pro-Khalistan leader, has launched an indefinite hunger strike in Dibrugarh jail in Assam, along with nine fellow detainees.

title: Maha: Another hospital reports 18 deaths in 24 hours
description: Reactions started pouring in after NCP chief Sharad Pawar on Tuesday morning took to social media and expressed concerns over the death of eight patients at government medical college and hospital (GMCH), Aurangabad. He cited that this report has come within 24 hours of the Nanded’s Dr Shanakarrao Chavan GMCH reporting deaths of 24 patients including 12 infants.

title: Two arrested in Cryptocurrency scam of Himachal
description: DGP Sanjay Kundu said that SIT is closing in on the kingpins of crypto currency scams in Himachal Pradesh and is making all efforts to arrest the accused.

title: PM Modi says KCR wanted to join BJP-led NDA
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi revealed that Telangana chief minister K Chandrashekar Rao (KCR) wanted to join the BJP-led National Democratic Alliance after the Hyderabad Municipal Corporation elections, but Modi rejected the offer due to KCR's actions. Modi accused the BRS government in Telangana of misusing central funds and warned the people to be cautious of the Congress party, which he claimed was being supported by the BRS. He also criticized the Congress for attempting to divide the votes.

title: Kohli, Gill can make strong impressions in World Cup: Anjum
description: After a hiatus of 12 years, India are set to host the World Cup once again, starting October 5 in Ahmedabad. The team will be led by Rohit Sharma this time. India will enter the mega tournament as the frontrunners and hot favourites.

title: Relief for foreign students, on-job training program to continue in US
description: The US Supreme Court has declined to review a lower court decision upholding the Optional Practical Training (OPT) program, which allows international students to work in the US after completing their studies. The program, which is particularly popular among Indian students, provides post-qualification work opportunities and is a major attraction for foreign students.

title: 4 killed as 14-year-old opens fire at mall in Bangkok
description: Four people were killed and a few others injured after a 14-year-old suspected gunman opened fire at a luxury mall in Thailand's capital Bangkok on Tuesday.The Thai police have taken the suspected teen shooter into custody.The Metropolitan Police Detective Department said on its Facebook page that the 14-year-old was being questioned over the incident at the Siam Paragon mall.

title: Cong's Singhvi differs with Rahul on 'population-based rights'
description: Senior Congress leader Abhishek Manu Singhvi has disagreed with Rahul Gandhi's idea of giving rights based on population and warned that such a move could lead to majoritarianism. Prime Minister Narendra Modi also criticized the idea, questioning if it would be fair to give rights according to population. The release of the Bihar caste survey results has renewed demands for a national caste census. The BJP has accused the opposition of trying to divide society along caste lines.

title: 'Disappearing' generals: Why Xi doesn’t trust his own military
description: China's defense minister, Li Shangfu, has been missing from public life for over a month, raising questions about the extent of President Xi Jinping's control over the military. This follows the disappearance of other officials, including the foreign minister. Chinese officials disappearing or being removed from posts more frequently now suggests that Xi's influence may not be as absolute as perceived.

title: 7 more deaths reported from Nanded hospital; 31 dead in 2 days
description: The District Information Office (DIO) of Nanded, located around 280 km from Aurangabad, confirmed this on a social media platform, which took the total count of the deceased patients in the hospital in 48 hours to 31.

title: 'Can rights be based on abadi?' PM Modi's dig at Cong
description: A day after the Bihar government released the state's caste survey, Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Tuesday took a sharp dig at Congress and asked the party whether rights can be given in proportion to "abadi" (population).Speaking at BJP's 'Parivartan Mahasankalp' rally in poll-bound Chhattisgarh's Jagdalpur, PM Modi asserted that poor people of the country have the first right over the nation's resources.

title: 2023 ODI World Cup: Top pacers to watch out for
description: The 2023 ICC ODI World Cup in India will showcase some of the world's best fast bowlers. Mitchell Starc, known for his lethal yorkers, has been a leading wicket-taker in previous World Cups. Jasprit Bumrah's precision yorkers and pace make him formidable. Mohammed Siraj, currently ranked as the No. 1 ODI bowler, has a stellar track record.

title: Pierre Agostini, Ferenc Krausz and Anne L’Huillier win Physics Nobel
description: The Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences on Tuesday awarded the 2023 Physics Nobel Prize to Pierre Agostini, Ferenc Krausz and Anne L’Huillier “for experimental methods that generate attosecond pulses of light for the study of electron dynamics in matter.”The physics prize comes a day after Hungarian-American Katalin Karikó and American Drew Weissman won the Nobel Prize in medicine for discoveries that enabled the creation of mRNA vaccines against Covid-19.

title: Strong tremors felt in Delhi-NCR, parts of north India after 6.2 earthquake jolts Nepal
description: Strong tremors were felt in the Delhi-NCR region and other parts of north India after a 6.2 earthquake rocked Nepal on Tuesday afternoon.The earthquake occured at a depth of 5km in the himalayan country.There were no immediate reports of damage or casualty.The tremors lasted nearly one minute and happened around 2.50pm.

title: Amitabh Bachchan, Rana Daggubati & Fahadh Faasil join Rajinikanth's 'Thalaivar 170'
description: Telugu star Rana Daggubati & Malayalam star Fahadh Faasil are the latest to join the star cast of Rajinikanth's 'Thalaivar 170' directed by  TJ Gnanvel.

title: Catholic priest joins BJP, church removes him from vicar duties
description: Fr Kuriakose Mattam received the primary membership of the BJP from the party's Idukki district president KS Aji on Monday.

title: Can deficiency of Vitamin D lead to cancer? Doctor explains
description: Although not a direct cause, a lack of vitamin D is thought to play a role in the onset and development of certain cancer forms.

title: SC posts hearing on Naidu's plea to October 9
description: ​​The Supreme Court directed the state government to file the documents placed on record before the high court to decide upon the applicability of section 17A of Prevention of Corruption (PC) Act.

title: Hyundai’s big safety push: All cars to get 6 airbags
description: Currently, 45 percent of Verna customers want the ADAS safety functions and are willing to pay for it. This is also reflected in the demand for top-end variants of Hyundai cars in recent years. Where top-end variants used to contribute to just 5 percent demand earlier,  demand for the fully loaded cars averages at about 22 percent across Hyundai's entire lineup in 2023.

title: Watch: Jimny tastefully modified into Mercedes-Benz G-Wagen
description: Despite the uncanny similarity in the appearance, it is still pretty easy for any enthusiast to tell that it is indeed a Maruti Suzuki Jimny under the skin, not a Mercedes-Benz G-Class. However, the tasteful conversion is a well-finished job, and truly makes the Jimny stand out.

title: Police searches Teesta Setalvad's house in Mumbai
description: Delhi Police's Special Cell conducted raids at 30 premises connected with online portal NewsClick and its journalists' houses, leading to outrage among journalists. The raids were also carried out at activist Teesta Setalvad's residence. Information and Broadcasting Minister Anurag Thakur defended the action, stating that investigative agencies have the freedom to conduct inquiries.

title: Encounter breaks out between terrorists, security forces in J&K Rajouri
description: A fierce anti-terror operation, involving heavy exchange of fire between terrorists and security forces, is under way in the Tattapani area of Kalakote in the Rajouri district of Jammu and Kashmir on Tuesday, according to officials.

title: Nitin Gadkari rides hydrogen bus in Prague
description: As a part of his trip to Prague, Nitin Gadkari took a test ride in a Skoda H'CITY hydrogen bus, showcasing the government's commitment to explore sustainable and eco-friendly mobility solutions for India.

title: Potential side effects of statins you need to be careful about
description: The UK's Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA) has advised patients with pre-existing myasthenia gravis to be cautious when taking statins, as there have been reports of new-onset or worsening of the condition. Myasthenia gravis is a neuromuscular disorder characterized by muscle weakness. Statins are medications used to lower cholesterol levels and reduce the risk of cardiovascular disease.

title: Crackdown on child marriage: Over 800 arrested in special operation in Assam
description: The development comes nearly three weeks after Assam chief minister Himanta Biswa Sarma warned that 3,000 people will be arrested in the state for their involvement in child marriages.

title: Jaiswal shines as India defeat Nepal in Asian Games opener
description: The Indian cricket team made a strong debut at the Asian Games with a 23-run victory against Nepal. Yashasvi Jaiswal played a brilliant inning, scoring a century in just 49 balls. India posted a formidable total of 202-4. Nepal struggled to chase the target and could only manage 179-9. Avesh Khan and Ravi Bishnoi stood out with three wickets each.

title: ODI World Cup: Long tail a big concern for India
description: India's tailenders in the upcoming ODI World Cup, including Jasprit Bumrah, have unimpressive batting averages and strike rates. This puts pressure on the top-order and allrounders. To compensate, India's top-order batsmen need to perform consistently, and the allrounders, such as Hardik Pandya and Ravindra Jadeja, need to contribute significantly with the bat.

title: Naidu fasts in jail, Lokesh leads hunger strike in Delhi
description: Nara Lokesh, the national general secretary of the Telugu Desam Party (TDP), spoke out against the criminalization of whistle-blowing in Andhra Pradesh. He participated in a hunger strike on Gandhi Jayanti to protest against false cases filed against his father and TDP chief, Nara Chandrababu Naidu. Lokesh criticized the YSRCP administration for arresting Naidu on false charges and vowed to fight the cases legally. TDP workers, including Naidu's wife Bhuvaneswari, also joined the hunger strike to show their support.

title: Couple poisons 3 daughters, stuffs bodies into trunk
India tells Canada to withdraw dozens of diplomatic staff: Report
ODI World Cup: Pace conundrum for Team India
description: India's pace bowling attack consisting of Mohammed Shami, Jasprit Bumrah, and Mohammed Siraj is believed to be the best in the business. However, the Indian team management has shown a tendency to use only two of these three bowlers together. Former India pacer Lakshmipathy Balaji believes that India should play all three pacers together in key games.

title: Delhi Police raid NewsClick's office, journalists
description: Delhi Police's Special Cell on Tuesday conducted raids at the places of news portal NewsClick and its journalists. Police recovered the dump data of laptops and mobile phones of some journalists of NewsClick. The Special Cell has registered a new case and started investigation.

title: Asiad: Yashasvi slams 48-ball century in India's opening match
description: Yashasvi Jaiswal, India's opener, made a remarkable 48-ball century in India's opening match against Nepal at the Hangzhou Asian Games. His impressive performance included seven sixes and eight elegant fours, leaving spectators and cricket enthusiasts in awe. However, his impressive performance was short-lived when he was caught at short third man.

title: One held from AP as NIA raids 62 locations in 2 Telugu states
Man takes Rs 20cr in loans using fake docus, held
Given ‘phenyl’ instead of vitamin, infant dies in hospital
description: The parents of an 11-month-old infant in Ahmedabad were shocked when their child began foaming at the mouth after being given phenyl instead of vitamin syrup by a nurse. The police have taken a complaint and are conducting an inquiry. If negligence is found, a case will be registered against the hospital staff or doctor involved. The bottle of medicine has been sent for forensic analysis. The hospital has faced previous complaints of negligence in the past.

title: Anurag Kashyap: There is a culture of Zameendari in the industry
description: Anurag Kashyap is known to speak his mind. In an exclusive conversation with ETimes, the filmmaker opened up about a short film he is producing, the culture of 'zameendari' in Bollywood, controversies and much more...

title: Punjab: Farm stubble burning continues, 119 cases reported
description: Stubble burning in Punjab is on the rise, with over 100 cases reported in a day for two consecutive days. As of Monday, there have been a total of 456 cases, surpassing the numbers from the previous two years. The district of Amritsar has reported the most number of cases, followed by Tarn Taran, Kapurthala, and Mohali. Stubble burning has been reported in 13 out of the 23 districts in Punjab.

title: Sanatan Dharma only religion in world: UP CM Yogi
description: Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath of Gorakhpur stated that there is only one religion in the world, Sanatan Dharma, while addressing a gathering at the Gorakhnath Temple. He emphasized the need for an open mind to understand the essence of the Srimadbhagawad Gita, stating that it cannot be confined to specific days or hours. Yogi Adityanath also highlighted the dedication of saints to the nation and society, mentioning the contributions of Mahant Digvijaynath in various religious and political endeavors. He emphasized that ashrams were once centers for scientific research.

title: Bangladesh woman returns after she finds her lover married
description: When Dilruba Sharmi, 32, a beautician from Bangladesh's Chittagong, and Abdul Karim, 27, who works as a chef in Bahrain, walked away from each other one last time in UP's Bahraich on Sunday, Sahir's immortal words came alive: "Chalo ek baar phir se ajnabi ban jayein hum dono... (Let's be strangers once again)."

title: Will share economic data of survey today: Bihar CM Nitish Kumar
description: Bihar Chief Minister Nitish Kumar has announced that the findings of the caste survey will be shared with nine political parties during a meeting. He also mentioned that the report on the economic condition of the people will be released at the same meeting. Nitish Kumar expressed his confidence that the Bihar caste survey will lead to a nationwide census of all social groups.

title: 4-year-old tries to open fridge in supermarket, electrocuted
description: A four-year-old girl in Hyderabad was electrocuted while trying to open a refrigerator at a local supermarket. The incident occurred when the child's parents were busy clearing the bill. The girl walked towards the refrigerator, but her mother brought her back. Moments later, she went back to the fridge and suffered a shock when she touched the door. The child was immediately rushed to the hospital but was declared dead on arrival. The supermarket staff discovered that the fridge was not properly grounded, leading to the tragedy. A criminal case has been registered against the supermarket.
